Money&nbsp;and power wrangles are&nbsp;now threatening the once&nbsp;vibrant law society of Kenya.&nbsp;The operations of the body are now grounded due to infighting between the president Nelson Havi and the Chief Executive Officer Mercy Wambua. And as&nbsp;KTN senior political reporter&nbsp;Geff Kirui now tells us, a section of members of the embattled society are now pushing for a caretaker leadership to take charge.